FT  23 SEP 94 / World News in Brief: Singapore drug hanging
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A 59-year-old Dutchman, Johannes van Damme, was hanged at Singapore's Changi
prison after being convicted of heroin trafficking. He was the first
westerner executed by the city-state for violating anti-drug laws.
