FT  22 SEP 94 / International Capital Markets: Vietnam opens up share sale
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HANOI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Vietnam is to allow foreigners to buy bonds and shares issued by state-owned
companies in what one economist said was a form of privatisation, Reuter
reports from Hanoi.
The scheme will be open to foreign companies and residents, overseas
Vietnamese and Vietnamese enterprises.
A government economist said the share issue would amount to issuing new
capital that would be privately held, diluting state ownership.
New regulations say the purchase and sale of bonds and shares should be in
Vietnamese dong.
