<HEADLINE>
FT  22 SEP 94 / Ministers blamed over rail dispute
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Delegates approved a motion condemning the government for 'prolonging the
rail strike'.
Mr Nick Harvey, MP for North Devon and industry spokesman, said the dispute
was close to being settled in June when ministers intervened. He maintained
that the government's intransigence would be responsible for the increase in
fares likely after a settlement.
