<HEADLINE>
FT  22 SEP 94 / TSB vote backs strike action
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Bifu, the banking and finance union, is to discuss plans for a series of
selective strikes after staff at TSB voted narrowly to back industrial
action over pay. The union has rejected a 2 per cent imposed pay package
that also includes plans for performance-related pay.
The union's TSB section council will next week seek the endorsement of the
full executive for a series of selective strikes. Members voted by 3,073 to
2,980 to back action in a 41 per cent turnout.
