<TEXT>
Legislation to prevent strikes in essential services, rather than simply to
limit their duration, has been urged on Mr Michael Portillo, the employment
secretary, by the Institute of Directors, Lisa Wood writes.
Recently the Confederation of British Industry, which is composed generally
of larger companies, suggested that the unions should have to hold
'refresher ballots' of members during long disputes.
