CBI's approach in a letter to Mr Portillo. 'In our view this would be
closing the stable door after the horse had bolted,' he said, adding: 'We
believe the situation requires more substantial measures.' He recommended
no-strike deals and binding arbitration as part of the rail sell-off
process.
