</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A liquidator is to be appointed to loss-making state-owned Irish Steel after
directors recommended the closure of its Cork-based steel plant - Ireland's
only steel mill - causing the loss of 520 jobs. Mr Ruairi Quinn, minister
for enterprise and employment, accepted the board's advice to call in the
liquidator after meeting Mr Pat Dineen, Irish Steel chairman, and Mr Leslie
Buckley, acting chief executive, last night. The closure follows the failure
of the company to win agreement from its craft unions on a survival plan
which has been backed by the board, the government, the Irish Congress of
Trade Unions and other Irish Steel workers.
