FT  22 SEP 94 / World News in Brief: Missing link unearthed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fossilised remains 4.4m years old of man's earliest direct ancestor have
been found in Ethiopia. The remains are almost 1m years older than the
previous earliest-known human ancestor and are thought to be the missing
link in the evolutionary chain.
